<p>SMA, 1954 - attempt towards UCC (as marriages are NOT governed by personal laws)</p>
<p>Treats interfaith marriages as secular</p>
<h3>OBJECTIVE</h3>
<p>&nbsp;establish marraige as secular institution (away from relgion)</p>
<p>Irrespective of religion and faith but conditions -&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Provisions&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>18F, 21M&nbsp;</li>
<li>prohibitions under act = ..?</li>
<li>has divorce provisions too</li>
<li>no provision for punishment for <u><em>forced conversion.</em></u></li></ol>
<h3>Religious conversions&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>If not by free will can create law n order - SC&nbsp;</li></ol>
<h3>Views of leaders on inter faith marriage ,&nbsp;</h3>
<p>In Annihilation of Caste, B.R. Ambedkar argues that inter­dining had not been success­ful in killing the spirit of caste and that the “real remedy is intermar­riage”</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In his book, Wo­men Enslaved (translated by G. Aloysius), Periyar to say that “no third person has any right to constrain or decide” the coming together of two people.</p>
<p>WOMEN's CHOICE IN MARRIAGE =&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>Periyar recast marriage as “life partnership agreements” wherein the two partners would come together on equal terms, and conducted thousands of self-respect marriages.</li></ul>
